text.section:
The Commission may:
except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, name and rename any street or highway and number and renumber the houses in the metropolitan district if each new number or change of number is reported to the owner or occupant of the building for the purpose of:
correcting mistakes;
removing confusion because of a duplication of street names; and
securing a uniformity of street names and numbering of houses;
place or have placed new numbers on the buildings or premises and proper signs indicating the names of streets and highways; and
appropriate and expend as much of any surplus from fees for building permits issued in each county as is necessary to pay for the expenses in carrying out this section.
